      "body": "pullback_preservesFiniteLimits: prove via flat extendScalars, NOT adjointness\n\n`pullback_preservesFiniteLimits` (`CechHigherDirectImageUnconditional.lean:193`, instance, `[Flat g]`) is a **true** statement but a genuine open `sorry` \u2014 do not attempt a cheap adjointness proof.\n\n- The statement is sound: module pullback $g^*$ = inverse image $g^{-1}$ (exact) followed by $-\\otimes_{\\mathcal O_S}\\mathcal O_{S'}$, which is left-exact **because** `[Flat g]`. Finite limits are preserved.\n- The trap: `g^*` is a **left adjoint**, so it preserves colimits / is right-exact \u2014 that gives you nothing for finite *limits*. \"Left adjoint $\\Rightarrow$ left-exact\" is backwards. The flatness hypothesis is doing all the work and must be used.\n- Intended route (per the leaf's own docstring): transfer along `SheafOfModules.pullbackIso`, discharge `forget`/`sheafification` (already limit-preserving in Mathlib), reduce to `ModuleCat.preservesFiniteLimits_extendScalars_of_flat` stalkwise. Reference Stacks 02KH.\n- Note it is a global `instance` carrying a sorry; `pullback_preservesHomology` (line 197) derives from it by `inferInstance`, so the whole flat-homology chain rests on this node.",
